  "doc_id": "173",
  "text": "We evaluate our approach on two large-scale multi-view datasets, Human3.6M [CITATION_1] and TotalCapture [CITATION_2] : we outperform the state-of-the-art methods when additional training data is not available, both in terms of speed and accuracy. When additional 2D annotations can be used [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , our accuracy remains comparable to that of the state-of-theart methods, while being faster. Finally, we demonstrate that our approach can handle viewpoints that were never seen during training. In short, we can achieve real-time performance without sacrificing prediction accuracy nor viewpoint flexibility, while other approaches cannot.",
